# =============================================================================
# FounderFlow — Tier 2 env separation
#
# This file used to be the single source of env truth. It now points you at
# the right per-environment template instead, so there's no way to
# accidentally copy prod credentials into a local `.env.local`.
#
# Pick the file that matches what you're setting up:
#
#   • Local development         → cp .env.local.example .env.local
#       Uses the docker-compose Postgres on 127.0.0.1:5433. Never touches
#       prod. Get running: `docker compose up -d && npm run db:migrate:local`
#
#   • Staging (Vercel Preview)  → cp .env.staging.example .env.staging
#       Points at a distinct staging Supabase project. CI runs
#       `prisma migrate deploy` against this on every merge to main.
#
#   • Production                → managed in Vercel's env-var UI only.
#       We deliberately do NOT keep prod values in a local file — see
#       CLAUDE.md "Database safety" for the incident history that led here.
#
# The old workflow (single `.env` pointing at Supabase prod) is what caused
# the account-wipe incident. Do not resurrect it.
# =============================================================================
